cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.DM. 

The paper studies the hardness and approximation algorithms for the $k$-Center problem on inputs that model transportation networks, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the planar graphs, low doubling metrics, and bounded highway dimension graphs, which are related to graph theory and combinatorics, so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also possible sub-categories.
